WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.600
So before I was differentiated into the lymphoma world, I did some myeloma, and this is our

00:00:07.600 --> 00:00:13.360
IST of having MRD-adaptive outpatient treatment with L-renanthamab.

00:00:13.360 --> 00:00:18.500
So I wanted to introduce you to our study at UCSD.

00:00:20.060 --> 00:00:21.720
These are my financial disclosures.

00:00:23.040 --> 00:00:30.340
So after three days of watching everyone's talks, I felt obligated to have a slide made

00:00:30.340 --> 00:00:31.380
by ChatGPT.

00:00:31.800 --> 00:00:38.820
So this is just added yesterday, but I think we've already talked a lot this session and

00:00:38.820 --> 00:00:45.000
also in the past few sessions about how it is important that we move our biospecific

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:46.760
therapies to the outpatient setting.

00:00:47.140 --> 00:00:51.400
And I feel like our first two speakers already saw my slides, and I don't really have much

00:00:51.400 --> 00:00:51.940
to add.

00:00:52.340 --> 00:00:53.020
But here.

00:00:53.040 --> 00:00:59.060
Improved access to care, of course, in the community, and then also cost savings.

00:00:59.060 --> 00:01:05.100
That is, I think, very elegantly illustrated by Mohamed, and also optimizing hospital bed

00:01:05.100 --> 00:01:05.640
utilization.

00:01:06.060 --> 00:01:12.100
We have all these patients who are in the hospital for about a week, and hopefully nothing's

00:01:12.100 --> 00:01:17.180
happening to them, but then we could have improved our hospital bed utilization.

00:01:18.960 --> 00:01:22.680
So again, this is already introduced to you all.

00:01:22.880 --> 00:01:23.020
But.

00:01:23.040 --> 00:01:25.180
So, again, I think it's important to note that the prophylactic tocilizumab administration

00:01:25.180 --> 00:01:35.260
has probably been an important kind of a step to mitigate CRS in this real-world study

00:01:35.260 --> 00:01:41.340
by 119 patients who are treated with outpatient multiple myeloma bispecific therapies with

00:01:41.340 --> 00:01:50.180
ELRA, TEC, TALC, and limvoceltumab, received a tocilizumab one hour prior to their first

00:01:50.180 --> 00:01:50.900
step-up dose.

00:01:51.720 --> 00:01:52.660
And remarkably.

00:01:53.040 --> 00:01:59.140
The CRS only happened in 10.1%, which is a significant reduction compared to what's

00:01:59.140 --> 00:02:03.140
reported, and the ICANS was 5.9%, which is about the same.

00:02:03.380 --> 00:02:07.580
There's also that, you know, concern that if you give tocilizumab that there are increased

00:02:07.580 --> 00:02:09.420
risk of ICANS, but they didn't see that.

00:02:09.960 --> 00:02:12.080
And majority were grade one CRS.

00:02:12.380 --> 00:02:16.320
And I think very importantly, no additional doses of tocilizumab or corticosteroids was

00:02:16.320 --> 00:02:19.460
given for CRS in this patient court.

00:02:19.920 --> 00:02:22.880
I think that's really important in bringing this to the community.

00:02:23.320 --> 00:02:29.680
So that you could potentially, in the future, decrease the need for daily monitoring and

00:02:29.680 --> 00:02:30.760
be more comfortable with that.

